Da-Yea Song

My research focuses on unraveling the complexities of brain development in autism and its developmental trajectories through the integration of genetic, neuroimaging, and behavioral data. I am also dedicated to exploring the interplay between mental and physical health to enhance well-being in individuals and families affected by neurodevelopmental disorders.

Education

Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health | Baltimore, MD
Ph.D.in Mental Health (Expected 2027)

University College London | London, UK
MSc in Advanced Neuroimaging (2021)

Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health | Baltimore, MD
MHS in Mental Health (2018)

Sogang University | Seoul, South Korea
BA in Psychology (2017)

Research Experience

Seoul National Bundang Hospital | Research Staff | 2019-2021

Kennedy Krieger Institute | Research Assistant | 2018-2019

Wendy Klag Center | Student Trainee | 2017-2018
